.TH VALIDATE\-PROFILE 1 "2026-04-04" "machine-setup 2.0" "Machine Setup Manual"
.SH NAME
validate\-profile.sh \- validate profile configuration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B validate\-profile.sh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates a profile configuration file for correctness. Checks that all
required fields are present, dotfile source paths exist, package references
resolve to known entries in the package configuration files, and inherited
profiles are valid.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Profile to validate.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show the help message and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Profile is valid.
.TP
.B 1
Validation errors found (missing fields, broken paths, unknown packages).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Validate the full profile:
.B validate\-profile.sh \-\-profile full
.TP
Validate a custom profile:
.B validate\-profile.sh \-\-profile mysetup
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR setup.sh (1)
.SH AUTHORS
Machine Setup contributors.
